# uv
# uv.lock IS tracked (reproducibility). Python venv is not.

# Data artifacts — never commit. WRDS terms + disk size both forbid it.
# Two-step rule: (1) ignore everything *inside* the repo-root data/ directory,
# (2) un-ignore the curated data/reference/ subtree. The leading slash anchors
# to repo root — without it the rule would also catch src/aegis/data/, which
# would silently drop the data module from commits (this happened in Week 1).
# Per-extension rules (*.parquet, *.sqlite, …) provide defense in depth so a
# stray data artifact outside /data/ is also caught.
/data/*
!/data/reference/

# Generated provenance sidecars for *.parquet artifacts (Day 9 onward) stay
# in lockstep with their parquet siblings: the sp500_membership.meta.json
# sidecar IS tracked (its CSV is checked in); the ticker_metadata.meta.json
# sidecar is NOT tracked (its parquet is gitignored).
/data/reference/ticker_metadata.meta.json

*.parquet
*.arrow
*.feather
*.duckdb
*.duckdb.wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite-journal
*.db

